15/09/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- For the second time in as many days Wednesday (14 September), the chamber of deputies rejected a motion for a no confidence vote against the government. This time it was the opposition Social Democratic Party that submitted the motion; a previous one was filed by the ultranationalist Greater Romania Party against Agriculture Minister Gheorghe Flutur. 
In other news, Romania and Turkey signed a protocol Wednesday for co-operation in the area of environmental protection. The document provides for the adoption of a common policy to reduce water pollution and regulate fishing in the Black Sea. (Nine o'clock - 15/09/05)
